# Quick Workflow Reference

## Pipeline Flow
Topic → YouTube Search → Select References → Get Transcripts →
Analyze (Gemini) → Generate Outline → Write Script (Gemini) →
Fact-Check → TTS (ElevenLabs) → Video (Veo+Remotion) →
Show Notes (Gemini) → Deliver

## Key Integration Points
- **YouTube API**: Search & captions (English only)
- **Gemini 3**: Analysis, outline, script, show notes
- **ElevenLabs**: Script → Audio (MP3/WAV)
- **Veo**: Script segments → HD video clips (5-6 scenes, 5s each)
- **Remotion**: Audio + slides/animations → Final video

## Output Requirements
- Audio file (MP3/WAV)
- Video file (MP4, 9:16 vertical format preferred)
- Show notes with timestamps (Markdown format)

## Data Flow
Each module takes input from the previous step and produces output for the next:
- Discovery produces list of YouTube videos
- Selection produces filtered list of references
- Transcription produces raw text
- Analysis produces themes and key points
- Outline produces structured episode plan
- Script produces conversational narrative
- TTS produces audio file
- Video produces visual content
- Show notes produces formatted summary

